==English==

===Etymology===
From [[root]] + [[kit]]

===Noun===
'''rootkit'''

#{{cattag|Computing}}: a collection of programs injected into a computer via a [[trojan]] or a [[backdoor]] by a criminal, to disallow analysis and tracking of the criminal's handiwork by the user of the computer. The word "root" is a designation from UNIX of the user with the highest rank and access to a computer system, a "rootkit" is a collection of programs that disallows the "root" user from observing the computers misuse by a criminal and allows the criminal to perform other activities such as changing account permissions, erasing files, configuring servers, installing viruses, stealing credit card numbers and so forth. More can be found on [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rootkit rootkits at wikipedia]. 

